Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback objects, override `OnStopped` on `Window` — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => SaveState(); // both platforms
    return window;
}
```

**Key notes:**
- `OnPause` (Android) = lost focus but may still be visible → maps to `Deactivated`
- `OnStop` (Android) / `DidEnterBackground` (iOS) = fully hidden → maps to `Stopped`
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR/watchdog kills
- On Android, also handle `Destroying` — the back button can skip `Stopped`
